  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-xs-offset-0 col-sm-offset-1 col-sm-10">
      <h2>Collect Observations</h3>
      <p>After creating a session record, you are ready to start observing.</p>
      <h3>Submitting an Observation</h3>
      <p>All <span class="highlight">observations are automatically submitted at the end of a session</span>. In other words, no action is required in order to record an observation</span> because of the built-in auto-submit feature, which occurs when no
        time remains in a given interval.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-xs-offset-0 col-sm-offset-1 col-sm-5">
      <h3>Start Timer</h3>
      <p>When you are ready to start, click the "Start Timer" button to begin. At this point, the timer will start counting down by the interval you included in the sessions create form.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-xs-offset-0 col-sm-offset-0 col-sm-5">
      <div class="tutorial-image-container">
        <p class="image-caption">Need Image</p>
        <img src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/13546265/25744399/bcec05c0-3167-11e7-911e-487aec6fa5e2.png" alt="Start Timer">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-xs-offset-0 col-sm-offset-1 col-sm-5">
      <h3>Time Interval Indicators</h3>
      <p>There are two indicators for time remaining in a given interval. The first lists the number of seconds remaining before the response is recorded. The second is a time bar which decreases in size as the interval comes to an end. This bar also changes
        color from green to red depending on the time remaining in an interval.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-xs-offset-0 col-sm-offset-0 col-sm-5">
      <div class="tutorial-image-container">
        <p class="image-caption">Need Image</p>
        <img src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/13546265/25744197/8a9fa212-3166-11e7-8466-2c162d69f5ae.png" alt="Time Interval Indicators">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-xs-offset-0 col-sm-offset-1 col-sm-5">
      <h3>Target vs. Random Peer Indicators</h3>
      <p>BOSS requires that a random peer be observed every 5th interval. There are two indicators to help the observer montor which student to observe. First, either "Observing: Target Student" or "Observing: Random Peer" will appear above the timer countdown.
        In addition, <span class="highlight">the background color changes to orange
        whenever a random peer is the student being observed during an interval</span>. This decreases the likelihood that the observer will make an error in observing the wrong student during an interval.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-xs-offset-0 col-sm-offset-0 col-sm-5">
      <div class="tutorial-image-container">
        <p class="image-caption">Need Image</p>
        <img src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/13546265/25744197/8a9fa212-3166-11e7-8466-2c162d69f5ae.png" alt="Target vs. Random Peer Indicators">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-xs-offset-0 col-sm-offset-1 col-sm-5">
      <h3>Updating a Submission</h3>
      <p>If an error is made by the observer when recording the observed behavior, the user can update the previous interval's submission. This can be accomplished by clicking the "edit" button for the last submission table. At this point, the observe
        can check a box if a behavior was observed, or uncheck a box if the behavior was not observed.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-xs-offset-0 col-sm-offset-0 col-sm-5">
      <div class="tutorial-image-container">
        <p class="image-caption">Updating a Submission</p>
        <img src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/13546265/25744197/8a9fa212-3166-11e7-8466-2c162d69f5ae.png" alt="Updating a Submission">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-xs-offset-0 col-sm-offset-1 col-sm-5">
      <h3>No Submission Warning</h3>
      <p>If an interval ends without at least one category being selected, the background for the last entry table turns red. This increases the likelihood that an observe will notice that nothing was submitted for a previous interval.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-xs-offset-0 col-sm-offset-0 col-sm-5">
